Groucho said that?

1165
01:45:09,220 --> 01:45:11,722
Call the <i>Times,</i> nail it to the goddamn door.

1166
01:45:11,889 --> 01:45:13,599
CIA are the good guys.

1167
01:45:13,766 --> 01:45:15,601
The Canadians are the good guys.

1168
01:45:15,768 --> 01:45:17,478
Yeah, we're not greedy. Them too.

1169
01:45:18,229 --> 01:45:22,733
Only. Canada takes the credit,
or they retaliate against the hostages.

1170
01:45:23,567 --> 01:45:25,402
Great Satan wasn't involved.

1171
01:45:26,153 --> 01:45:28,155
No CIA.

1172
01:45:28,364 --> 01:45:29,907
Is that right, Jack?

1173
01:45:32,076 --> 01:45:33,786
Involved in what?

1174
01:45:34,787 --> 01:45:37,289
We were as surprised as anybody.

1175
01:45:40,251 --> 01:45:41,961
Thank you, Canada.

1176
01:45:42,169 --> 01:45:44,839
MacDonald:
<i>We knew that each day they stayed there...</i>

1177
01:45:45,005 --> 01:45:47,675
<i>...the danger was becoming greater.</i>

1178
01:45:47,883 --> 01:45:51,929
<i>We had been looking for a solution to have them
leave the country during the past three months.</i>

1179
01:45:52,096 --> 01:45:54,765
<i>Day 87, and finally a sliver
of really good news.</i>

1180
01:45:54,932 --> 01:45:58,727
The U.S. Department of State
hereby honors Joe Stafford...

1181
01:46:00,229 --> 01:46:01,647
...Kathy Stafford...

1182
01:46:02,940 --> 01:46:04,650
...Mark Lijek...

1183
01:46:05,276 --> 01:46:10,489
<i>We Americans will be forever grateful
to our great friend and ally to the north...</i>

1184
01:46:10,656 --> 01:46:14,910
<i>...for the protection and the safe passage
provided for our diplomats.</i>

1185
01:46:15,077 --> 01:46:16,328
Bob Anders.

1186
01:46:16,495 --> 01:46:19,206
<i>Here, or anywhere in the world...</i>

1187
01:46:19,373 --> 01:46:20,958
<i>...Canada will pay...</i>

1188
01:46:22,293 --> 01:46:26,297
<i>...for this violation
of the sovereignty of Iran.</i>

1189
01:46:26,463 --> 01:46:30,676
<i>Thank you to Pat and Ken Taylor
and the great nation of Canada.</i>

1190
01:46:34,513 --> 01:46:37,224
So I'm sitting in Jerry's this morning,
I'm having breakfast.

1191
01:46:37,391 --> 01:46:40,477
Waitress comes over to me,
she's waving a newspaper, and she says:

1192
01:46:40,644 --> 01:46:44,023
"You see what those Canadians pulled off?
Why can't we do something like that?"

1193
01:46:44,815 --> 01:46:46,650
And I said to her-- Do you know what I said?

1194
01:46:47,067 --> 01:46:48,193
No, what?

1195
01:46:48,736 --> 01:46:50,195
"Argo fuck yourself."

1196
01:47:18,974 --> 01:47:20,017
All set.

1197
01:47:20,976 --> 01:47:22,353
Thanks a lot.

1198
01:47:33,489 --> 01:47:34,490
Ha!

1199
01:47:35,866 --> 01:47:39,370
Heh. And I left my autograph book at home.

1200
01:47:45,000 --> 01:47:46,710
His Eminence called me.

1201
01:47:46,877 --> 01:47:48,087
He wants to see you.

1202
01:47:48,587 --> 01:47:50,297
Probably wants to fire me himself.

1203
01:47:51,423 --> 01:47:53,759
He wants to give you the Intelligence Star.

1204
01:47:54,969 --> 01:47:56,804
You're getting the highest award of merit...

1205
01:47:57,012 --> 01:48:00,349
...of the Clandestine Services
of these United States.

1206
01:48:01,308 --> 01:48:03,227
Ceremony's on the 14th.

1207
01:48:03,394 --> 01:48:06,563
If they push it a week, I can bring lan.
That's his winter break.

1208
01:48:08,065 --> 01:48:12,403
The op was classified,
so the ceremony's classified.

1209
01:48:12,569 --> 01:48:15,614
He can't know about it.
Nobody can know about it.

1210
01:48:17,157 --> 01:48:20,244
So they're just gonna give me an award
and then they're gonna take it back.

1211
01:48:20,828 --> 01:48:21,870
That's right.

1212
01:48:23,747 --> 01:48:26,083
If we wanted applause,
we would've joined the circus.

1213
01:48:27,793 --> 01:48:29,920
- I thought we did.
- Ha.

1214
01:48:30,587 --> 01:48:33,382
Carter said you were a great American.

1215
01:48:34,091 --> 01:48:35,759
Great American what?

1216
01:48:36,301 --> 01:48:37,761
He didn't say.

1217
01:48:51,108 --> 01:48:52,359
What happened to your picture?

1218
01:48:53,986 --> 01:48:55,195
It's in turnaround.

1219
01:49:37,488 --> 01:49:39,073
Can I come in?

1220
01:50:25,077 --> 01:50:35,879
The Iran Hostage crisis ended on January 20, 1981, when all
remaining hostages were released. They spent <i>444</i> days in captivity.

1221
01:50:37,422 --> 01:50:47,558
The involvement of the C.I.A. complemented efforts of the Canadian embassy in freeing the six held in Tehran.
To this day, this story stands as an enduring model for international cooperation between governments.

1222
01:50:48,976 --> 01:50:55,399
All of the Houseguests returned to the U.S.
Foreign service after their ordeal in Iran

1223
01:50:56,942 --> 01:51:06,910
Oscar-winning makeup artist John Chambers was awarded the C.I.A.'s intelligence Medal,
its highest civilian honor. He and Mendez remained friends until Chambers! death in 2001.

1224
01:51:08,704 --> 01:51:15,669
Tony Mendez's intelligence Star was returned to him in 1997,
when the Argo operation was declassified by President Clinton.

1225
01:51:25,721 --> 01:51:33,687
He lives in rural Maryland with his family.

1226
01:53:26,133 --> 01:53:31,138
<i>They went in, as you know, under
the guise of creating a motion-picture film.</i>

1227
01:53:31,346 --> 01:53:35,976
<i>But that it had a very high possibility
of failure.</i>

1228
01:53:36,143 --> 01:53:38,437
<i>And after it was successful, of course...</i>

1229
01:53:38,603 --> 01:53:41,398
<i>...it was a great temptation
to reveal all the stories...</i>

1230
01:53:41,565 --> 01:53:44,985
<i>...so maybe I could take a little bit
of credit for it, since I was president...</i>

1231
01:53:45,152 --> 01:53:49,740
<i>...but we had to keep it secret.
Tony Mendez has gone down in CIA history...</i>

1232
01:53:49,906 --> 01:53:51,783
<i>...after his retirement...</i>

1233
01:53:51,950 --> 01:53:58,790
<i>...as one of the 50 most important
CIA operatives of all time.</i>

1234
01:53:59,416 --> 01:54:04,796
<i>Eventually we got every hostage
back home, safe and sound...</i>

1235
01:54:04,963 --> 01:54:08,967
<i>...and we upheld the integrity of our country,
and we did it peacefully.</i>
